<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Refugees Receive Financial Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Relief
Organization has announced that it has given more than 4 million
Birr (about 950,000 US Dollars) to 2,704 Ethiopian refugees
repatriated from the Sudan and settled in northern Gondar area.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Ambasaw Araya, coordinator of the
Gondar returnee affairs office of the organization.
</P>
<P>
The coordinator said, another 5,707 returnees have been
provided with 5,770 quintals of grain and 28,850 litres of edible
oil.
</P>
<P>
About 21,065 Ethiopian refugees have been repatriated between
December and March this year under an agreement and a program
jointly organized by the Ethiopian government and the United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees. Another 40,000 Ethiopian
refugees will be returned home before June, this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
