<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Buthelezi Always Cooperates: Mandela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela today praised his black rival Inkatha Freedom
Party (IFP) leader and Home Affairs Minister Mangosuthu Buthelezi
for being cooperative whenever differences between them needed to
be ironed out.
</P>
<P>
Mandela was reacting to statements made by Buthelezi on Friday
that the May 29 local government elections in Kwazulu/Natal
Province should go ahead and not be postponed or staggered.
</P>
<P>
Mandela and Buthelezi discussed on the phone yesterday the
situation in Kwazulu/Natal which might jeapordize the holding of
the forthcoming local polls.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders agreed to meet in Cape Town next week to
discuss violence and voter registration irregularities in the
province.
</P>
<P>
The president said the possible staggering or postponement of
the polls should be considered in consultation with the effected
political parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
