<HEADLINE> Roundup: Israel Continues Aggressions against South Lebanon (Part I) (by Shao Jie) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Israeli forces today carried out
more air raids and bombardments at southern Lebanese villages,
killing seven people and wounding 19 others on the third
successive day of the Israeli agressions agaisnt Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Today's casualties added the number of victims of the Israeli
agressions in three days to 25 died and some 55 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 100,000 local residents from some 50
southern Lebanese towns and villages have been forced to leave
their houses to escape the Israeli air raids and bombardments.
</P>
<P>
In a bloodiest air raid today, Israeli helicopters opened fire
at an ambulance on the Hanniyeh road near in the Sour area in
south Lebanon around 2:00 p.m. local time (11:00 GMT), killing six
people, most of whom were children, and wounding six others.
</P>
<P>
Before this air raid, the Israeli warplanes also bombarded the
southern Lebanese villages of Haris, Zibgin, Shaitiyeh, Alasouani,
Tibnin, Shaqra, Barashit, Safad Al-Batikh.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in the South reported that the Israeli air
force totally carried out 16 air raids at targets in south Lebanon
since this morning, in an addition to bombardments at all the
villages opposite the Israeli-occupied buffer zone.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli bombardments led to the killing of one villagers,
Mohammed Abdul Karim,50, at Kafra, and the wounding of 13 others.
</P>
<P>
Latest reports from the South said that the Israeli occupation
forces bombarded sporadicly the southern Lebanese areas of
Nabatiyeh and Iglim Al-Toffah.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli warplanes also imposed a blockade upon Lebanon's
ports of Beirut, Saida and Sour and banned any ship from entering
the ports.
</P>
<P>
In response to today's Israeli aggression, the Islamic
Resistance, the military wing of Hezbollah, launched Katyusha
rockets at the Jewish settlements of Nahariyeh this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Resistance also announced that its guerrillas shot
down an Israeli military helicopter with Sam7 anti-air missiles
when the helicopter was launching an air raid at the southern
Lebanese village of As-Smaimyeh in Sour area.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri and Foreign Minister Farez
Boueiz Left here this afternoon for Damascus to meet with Syrian
leaders on continuous Israeli agressions against Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Hariri will visit Cairo and then Paris, to meet with
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and French President Jacques
Chirac within Lebanon's efforts in seeking an international
interference and condemnation against the Israeli escalations.
</P>
<P>
A Syrian-Lebanese enlarged summit, which had been scheduled to
be held in Damascus today, was canceled due to the Israeli
escalations.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
