<HEADLINE> .bjh:p:m:ye:E:xiao:96/04/13/20/20 afg041320hke -- Mandela Praises Former Posts Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's former Posts
and Telecommunications Minister Pallo Jordan was one of the most
capable leaders of the African National Congress, and could not
simply be thrown out into the streets, President Nelson Mandela
said today.
</P>
<P>
Mandela made the remarks at his official Cape Town residence.
Jordan was dismissed from the cabinet post in a cabinet reshuffle
announced by Mandela on March 28.
</P>
<P>
The president, who met Jordan on Friday, said his discussions
with Jordan about the future assignment were still "a very
sensitive matter".
</P>
<P>
However, agreement on Jordan's new assignment had yet to be
reached, Mandela said, adding "until we are able to reach some
agreement on his future assignment, it will be premature for me
to comment."
</P>
<P>
The president's office said yesterday in a statement the
meeting was one of "a series of private discussions to explore
various options regarding Jordan's new area of deployment".
</P>
<P>
"In the meantime Pallo Jordan will continue serving as a
member of parliament," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
However, Jordan declined to comment on his political future
after the discussions with Mandela. 
</P>
</TEXT>
