<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Rounds Off Official Visit to France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOULOUSE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng left
here for home this evening after a five-day official visit to
France during which he met French leaders and witnessed the
signing of commercial agreements worth 2.4 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure, he visited Aerospatiale, the French side
of the European four-nation aircraft consortium Airbus Industrie,
which China has signed up to build 33 Airbus commercial planes.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Li met with French President Jacques Chirac,
Prime Minister Alain Juppe and stressed the development of a
long-term partnership of friendly cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li also met with the president of the French National
Assembly, president of the French Senate and industrial and
commercial leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
