<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Regains 6.32 Birr:Dollar Exchange Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The National Bank of
Ethiopia announced in a press release today that with effect from
April 15, the applicable rate for all transactions outside the
auction shall be 6.32 Birr for one US Dollar.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that the exchange rate of Ethiopian
Birr has stayed at 6.32 for one US Dollar. The Birr devalued from
6.32 to 6.35 for one US Dollar from January to March this year.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian money valued from 6.35 to 6.32 Birr for one US
Dollar at the last auction held on March 30, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The National Bank of Ethiopia said the total amount of
foreign exchange made available at this morning's auction was 28
million US Dollars, adding that the highest bid rate on the
foreign exchange auction was 6.37 Birr whereas the lowest bid
rate was 6.27 Birr for one US Dollar.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian introduced a bi-weekly foreign exchange auction in
May, 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
