<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Starts Visit to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen left Paris for Macedonia on Saturday for a
three-day visit to broaden cooperation between China and the
Balkan republic.
</P>
<P>
Since setting up diplomatic relations in 1993, the two
countries have developed political, economic and cultural
exchanges. Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov met Chinese Premier
Li Peng in Copenhagen in March, 1995, and its former Foreign
Minister Stevo Crvenkovski visited China in the same year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government also sent several cultural and economic
delegations to the former Yugoslav republic, paving the way for
future cooperation.
</P>
<P>
However, bilateral trade between the two countries has not been
fully promoted because the Macedonian economy was seriously
affected by international sanctions imposed on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who accompanied Premier Li Peng to France, will also
visit Armenia, Georgia, Azerbaijan and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Qian will meet U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher,
British Foreign Secretary Malcolm Rifkind and Dutch Deputy Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Hans Van Mierlo in the Hague on
April 19-20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
