<HEADLINE> Zambian Ruling Party, Opposition Draw in By-elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian ruling Movement for
Multi- party Democracy (MMD) and the opposition United National
Independence Party (UNIP) won a seat respectively in Friday's
by-elections in two constituencies.
</P>
<P>
In Moomba constituency of Southern Province, UNIP veteran
politician Mainza Chona, once prime minister in the Kaunda
government, lost to MMD candidate Morries Moonga, who polled
1,410 votes against his 987 votes.
</P>
<P>
In Mkaika constituency of Eastern Province, UNIP candidate
Bernard Phiri beat MMD candidate James Phiri by 1,139 votes. The
UNIP candidate received 2,519 votes to gain the parliamentary
seat.
</P>
<P>
The by-elections in the two constituencies have been described by
the local press as incident free despite some short-comings here and
there. 
</P>
