<HEADLINE> Four Balkan States to Modernize Customs Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SKOPLJE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Four Balkan countries have signed
an agreement to modernize inter-border customs services, local press
said today.
</P>
<P>
The program, which will cost seven million U.S. dollars,
includes the reconstruction or expansion of three customs offices
on Macedonia's borders with Albania and Bulgaria and with the
Albanian port of Durres.
</P>
<P>
The up-grading of customs between Macedonia, Albania, Bulgaria
and Romania, one of the U.N.'s regional development programs, was
decided on in 1993 at a ministerial meeting in Rome of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe. 
</P>
