<HEADLINE> Moscow's Envoy Fails to Meet Dudayev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Fighting and bad weather in
Chechnya blocked face to face talks between Moscow's peace envoy
and Chechen separatist leader Dzhokhar Dudayev, Itar-Tass news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
But Rafael Khakimov, adviser to Moscow-appointed mediator
Tatar President Mintimer Shaimiyev, said talks with Dudayev's
personal aide Vagap Tutakov were a "positive step and evident
advancement."
</P>
<P>
Khakimov said his planned meeting with Dudayev had not taken
place due to "the fighting and rains that had made roads in
Chechnya impassable."
</P>
<P>
After his meeting with Tutakov, member of a contact group
preparing for negotiations between Moscow and Dudayev mediated by
Shaimiyev, Khakimov said, "It is not easy to speak with them (the
separatists), there are a number of problems, but I see the
prospects," the envoy said.
</P>
<P>
Itar-Tass reported that the rebels "did not refuse in principle
Tatar President Shaimiyev's mediating in negotiations with Moscow."
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin announced on March 31 a plan
for the peaceful settlement of the 16-month Chechen war which
included talks with Dudayev. 
</P>
</TEXT>
