<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 16:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Continues Attacking Hezbollah Targets in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli army today continued
air strikes against Hezbollah targets in the towns and villages in
southern Lebanon, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Israeli army helicopters attacked a number
of Hezbollah positions in southern Lebanon, while the Israeli
army artilleries increased their shelling on villages that provided
shelters to Hezbollah gunmen.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Lebanon said that two people were killed and
another wounded this afternoon when an Israeli helicopter
rocketed an ambulance in southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
However, an Israeli army spokesman announced that an Israeli
helicopter bombed a car belonging to a Hezbollah activist in
the Lebanese village of Hiniya, and it appeared that the
Hezbollah activist was wounded.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army said earlier that it would fire at every
suspicious vehicle traveling in southern Lebanon, and warned
people not to use the main coastal road linking southern
Lebanon to Beirut, capital of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
During the day, bad weather hampered Israeli air strikes
against Hezbollah targets, as a heavy fog over northern Israel
and southern Lebanon severely restricted visibility.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli army today once again called on residents of the
town and villages in southern Lebanon to leave the area by 4:15
p.m. local time (1315GMT), so as to avoid further civilian
casualties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Lebanese Radio reported that the Israeli Navy has
imposed a blockade around Beirut's harbor since 4:00 a.m.
(0100GMT) this morning, with its warships stopping ships
from entering all ports from Tyre to Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Israeli airplane also flew over Beirut this afternoon, and
the Lebanese authorities warned residents of the possibility of
new Israeli attacks on the southern suburb of the capital.
</P>
<P>
Reports indicated that about 20 people have been killed and
more than 40 others wounded in the Israeli military operation
against Hezbollah, which started Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, meanwhile, has been reporting of Katyusha rocket
attacks against northern Israel.
</P>
<P>
A senior Lebanese official said that more than 200,000
Lebanese residents have fled towns and villages in the
southern part of the country to escape the Israeli military
operation.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Lebanon, the Lebanese government has
formally requested the U.N. to launch international operation to
get humanitarian assistance for the Lebanese displaced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
