<HEADLINE> Chinese Divers Win More golds at Asian Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese divers won two more gold
medals to bring the team's gold medal tally to four at the Fifth
Asian Swimming Championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Lao Jiezhen, 13, won the women's platform with a total of
515.46 points, while Fan Huaqiang made a golden double, with his
victory in the men's three-meter springboard.
</P>
<P>
Lao, seventh at this year's national championships a week ago,
emerged from the field of nine with her more difficult dives and
consistent performance. She scored a day-high of 76.80 points for
her eighth dive, which helped her up to the top of final rankings
for the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Divers from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea took the
silver and bronze medals, with Ri Ok Rim collecting 509.61 and
Choe Myong Hwa taking 498.18 points.
</P>
<P>
China's Wang Xian finished fourth with 483.06 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese took the top two places in the men's three-meter
springboard final.
</P>
<P>
Fan became the championships' first double gold-medalist as he
swept the men's springboard titles.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Fan, winner of the one-meter event on Firday,
got 706.68 points to win the three-meter event final.
</P>
<P>
Fan's teammate Huang Wen, runner-up at Friday's one-meter
event, got a silver medal again after he collected 665.94 on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's Lee Jong-Hee was third with 634.41 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese diver Wu Shunqun took the women's one-meter springboard
event with 266.52 Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
