<HEADLINE> Greece to Promote Exports to Balkan Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Greek government will take
measures to help promote exports to the Balkan and Black Sea
countries, a senior Greek official said.
</P>
<P>
Deputy national economy minister responsible for foreign trade
issues, Manolis Beteniotis, told the Exports Promotion
Organization (ope) officials that the Greek government attaches
great importance to the support of the trade and investment
cooperation of the private sector in the new markets of the
countries in the Black Sea and Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
According to the local press today, on the instructions of the
government, ope is expected to submit a special action plan for
the promotion of economic activity in these countries, including
the establishment of new ope trading centres in these regions.
</P>
<P>
The action plan will call for a more active role of the state
through agencies like ope and the Export Credit Insurance
Organization in the promotion of Greek exports to these countries.
</P>
<P>
It will also include the restructuring ope's human resources
and the establishment of new offices, the expansion of Greece's
banking system to the Balkan countries and Russia, the granting of
export credits and the planning of cross-border cooperation with
Bulgaria and Albania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
