<HEADLINE> Chinese Divison Two Soccer League Kicks off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese division two soccer
league kicked off on Saturday with six visiting teams keeping
unbeaten.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning team, 10-time national champion which was relegated
this season, beat Vanguard 2-1 on the road match marred by fans'
riots in Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan fans, angered by a controversial goal by Liaoning 35
minutes into action, stampeded into the pitch, interrupting the
match for 38 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Foshan downed Shenyang 2-0, while Shanghai Pudong
held its cross-town rival Yuyuan to a goalless draw.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, relegated Qingdao Hainiu edged Dalian
Shunfa 1-0, Jiangsu Jinling drew Locomotive 1-1 and Henan tied
Hubei 0-0.
</P>
<P>
China's division one league opens on Sunday. 
</P>
