<HEADLINE> Russian Official Says Pyongyang Trip a Breakthrough </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Prime Minister
Vitaly Ignatenko today described his visit to the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) as "timely" and a "breakthrough."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Itar-Tass news agency, Ignatenko said,
"We are very satisfied that a visit at such a high level took
place after a long period of stagnation in our relations."
</P>
<P>
Ignatenko said the visit was "a serious breakthrough" in
relations between Moscow and Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
A Russian delegation, headed by Ignatenko, ended a three-day
official visit to the DPRK Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two sides held the first meeting of an
inter-government commission on trade, economic, scientific and
technical cooperation as well as political consultations. Deputy
foreign ministers of the two countries attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
In view of the recent tension on the Korean peninsula, the
Russian side urged restraint from both the DPRK and South Korea
and asked them to maintain the present armistice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
