<HEADLINE> Belgium Sacks National Soccer Team Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Belgian soccer governing
body has fired Paul Van Himst as national coach after his failure
to lead the team through to this summer's European championships.
</P>
<P>
Van Himst is to be replaced by assistant Wilfried Van Moer, the
Belgian soccer association said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Former Anderlecht star Van Himst, 52, took over as coach in May
1991 and led Belgium to the second stage of the 1994 World Cup
finals.  
</P>
