<HEADLINE> Romania Establishes First Nuclear Power Station </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Romania's first nuclear power
station started its test run today, representing a milestone in
the country's history of power generation.
</P>
<P>
The station's first nuclear reactor generating set will go
into formal operation in May and reach its design capacity of
700,000 kilowatts within three months.
</P>
<P>
The station, in the eastern city of Cernavoda, was inspected by
President Ion Iliescu in March and will be visited next Wednesday
by Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu and his Canadian counterpart,
Jean Chretien, whose country provided major equipment for the
station's five nuclear reactors.
</P>
<P>
However, an appropriate method for storing the station's
nuclear waste, has still not been found, local press reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
