<HEADLINE> Black to Meet Enqvist in Final of Indian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Byron Black of
Zimbabwe earned a spot in the final against top seed Thomas
Enqvist of Sweden after beating German Alex Radulescu on Saturday
in the Indian Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Black, world 32nd in the ATP computer rankings, downed the
21-year-old German 6-4, 6-4 in a semifinal match.
</P>
<P>
In the other semifinal, world number nine Enqvist defeated
American Jonathan Stark 7-6 (8/6), 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Stark, 140th-ranked player, was given a wild card entry into
the tournament after Australian Pat Cash pulled out with an injury.
</P>
<P>
The 139th-ranked Radulescu ousted second-seeded Wayne Ferreira
and Frenchman Jerome Golmard, the eighth seed, to reach the
semifinals but had no answer Saturday to Black's powerful
double-fisted groundstrokes from both sides.
</P>
<P>
Stark was also unable to match the power of the Enqvist, who
won five titles last year but will be playing in his first final
of the year here Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
