<HEADLINE> S. Arabia Concerned over Israeli Raids on Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today voiced its
profound concern over the recent Israeli air raids against Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
A Saudi Foreign Ministry official said that the Israeli air
raids constituted a violation of the Lebanese sovereignty, safety
and territorial integrity in defiance of its international
legitimacy.
</P>
<P>
According to the Saudi News Agency monitored here, the official
referred to U.N. Security Council resolution 425, which calls for
an unconditional withdrawal of the Israeli troops from south
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
"The continuation of the Israeli air raids on Lebanon will
result in more violent acts and unrest at a time when Saudi Arabia
is looking for achieving a just and comprehensive peace in the
region," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi official, whose name was not disclosed by the agency,
reiterated his country's solidarity with Lebanon in defending the
safety and security of the Lebanese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
