<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Aidid Retakes Huddor Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were
killed and 27 others were wounded when clashes erupted between
the militiamen of General Mohamed Farah Aidid and those of the
Rahanwein Resistance Army (RRA) at Bur Jebbo and Gof Gudud
villages on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Ali Aden Margus, political leader of the RRA, said the
shootout broke out after three technicals belonging to the
General attacked the villages near Baidoa, about 16 and 30 km
west of Baidoa respectively.
</P>
<P>
Mr Margus who spoke to reporters in north Mogadishu after the
incident, claimed to have overcome one armed wagon belonging to
Aidid. He also said two of his men were killed in the fighting
and that they are ready to take back Baidoa from General Aidid's
forces.
</P>
<P>
Mr Margus claimed that his forces ambushed three trucks
carrying logistics support for Aidid's men in Baidoa, taking away
fuel, ammunition, blankets and uniforms. However, he admitted
that all trucks have been recovered by militiamen of the general.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, supporters of General Aidid said their men
dispersed "foreign manipulated armed bandits" who attacked the
villages o inf Bur Jebbo and Gof Gudud on Friday with heavy
casualties inflicted on the enemy.
</P>
<P>
They said their forces have regained control of Huddor town,
which was also confirmed by RRA political leader Magus.
</P>
<P>
However, Mr Margus said his men are regrouping in the nearby
jungle in a bid to regain control of the town. 
</P>
</TEXT>
