<HEADLINE> mee041312hke-- Kuwait Holds Joint Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait today started the
second stage of the five-day "Ultimate Resolve" joint military
exercise at the Barrack of the Marty Brigade 35, participated by a
number of countries.
</P>
<P>
The Ultimate Resolve war games, whose first phase took place in
1994, are the largest military drills in the world with respect to
the number of troops and countries involved.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait News Agency today quoted Army Chief of Staff
General Ali Al-Mloumen as saying that "the first stage of the
military exercises was successful despite difficulties and
obstacles we faced during the war games."
</P>
<P>
He said that despite the diversity of the ethnic and religious
backgrounds, coordination among the allied forces became stronger
after five years of the Kuwait liberation war that forced Iraqi
forces to pull out of Kuwait in February, 1991.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed Russia, China and Italy which took part in the
exercises as observers for the first time. He hoped that these
countries will become actual participants in the coming stages of
the military exercises.
</P>
<P>
The general said the Kuwaiti national guards and army, interior
ministry forces and forces from the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC)
states, Egypt, Syria, the United States and France would
participate in the drills due to end on April 18.
</P>
<P>
The GCC groups Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Oman, Bahrain, the United
Arab Emirates and Qatar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
