<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 13:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> College Students Improving Their Behavior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nanning, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Avenues now are clear of even one
piece of litter, garbage cans which used to stand
higgledy-piggledy now stand tidily along the roadsides, and in the
dining hall students are in good order for their meals.
</P>
<P>
During study time the library and all the classrooms are filled
with busy students, and there are many students still studying in
their dormitories.
</P>
<P>
The Karaoke song and dance halls in the surrounding area of the
university, which were crowed and noisy previously, now have
become very quiet, and some have even closed down.
</P>
<P>
All these are indications of a new atmosphere at Guangxi
University in this capital of southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, as a result of an anti-uncivilized behavior
campaign, starting in March last year.
</P>
<P>
A year ago, when the new semester had just begun, the Students
Affairs Section together with the Youth League of the university,
listed 25 types of uncivilized behavior to be eliminated on the
campus.
</P>
<P>
Among the forbidden behaviors, booing and hooting at
gatherings, over-intimate contact with the opposite sex, doodling
and scribbling on desks and walls, and shining mirrors at the
opposite sex's dormitories came top of the list.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, campaigns to encourage self-cultivation and
good manners among the students were also carried out.
</P>
<P>
Regular heart-to-heart talks on selected topics between the
students and university leaders, for example, drew wide interest
and won high appraise from the students.
</P>
<P>
Dong Wenfang, a junior female student in the department of
chemistry, said she believed that "these efforts will play a
guilding role in modeling the students' outlook on both world and
life".
</P>
<P>
Chen Haihui, another junior student, in the department of
international trade, said, "At the beginning I felt that my
privacy was infringed upon and objected to those strict
regulations, but as time passed I came to understand that it will
finally benefit us students by creating a better general mood and
environment for us to study."
</P>
<P>
The significance of such a campaign is also found in the job
market. "Employers judge the students' quality by the general mood
of their university, and uncivilized behavior on campus will
greatly influence the students' chances in the job market," said
senior student Liu Ying, who is currently seeking a job.
</P>
<P>
According to Liang Qiguang, deputy Party secretary of Guangxi
University, it is the university's bounden duty to stress the
moral training of students. "Without a generation of successors
with good moral, intellectual and physical education, China will
not be able to achieve its long-term goal of stability and
development", he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
