<HEADLINE> Hainan Holds Fifth Coconut Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Hainan International
Coconut Festival, which opened this morning in this capital city
of south China's Hainan Province, will feature the island's
tropical scenery and cultural activities.
</P>
<P>
This makes a difference for the festival, as all the four
previous ones focused on business transactions and introduction of
overseas capital.
</P>
<P>
An island province on the southernmost tip of China, coconut is
the most famous of its special local products, and more or less a
symbol of the province.
</P>
<P>
As Hainan has been chosen as a key venue for the '96 China
Holiday program by China's tourism authorities, the current
coconut festival will include artistic and theatrical
performances, activities related to '96 China Holiday,
exhibitions, and economic and trade talks.
</P>
<P>
This year's festival will also mark the eighth anniversary of
the establishment of both Hainan Province and the Hainan Special
Economic Zone, China's biggest.
</P>
<P>
Since April 1, cultural and business activities related to the
festival have been carried out throughout the island. 
</P>
