<HEADLINE> Yunnan to Produce Titanium with Japanese Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan Province
will exploit its deposits of titanium on large scale, with
investment from Japanese businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The Kunming Lanyun Industry and Trade Company, the largest
seller in the province's titanium industry, has established a
joint venture with Japanese investors.
</P>
<P>
With an annual production capacity of 40,000 to 50,000 tons,
the venture will have a sales volume topping 30 million yuan
(about 3.6 million US dollars)-worth annually.
</P>
<P>
It is scheduled to go into operation this June, said Pan Yang,
chairman of the joint venture, noting that over 80 percent of its
products will be sold overseas.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan's proven reserves of titanium rank first in the
country. Titanium plays an important role in the aerospace,
aviation, navigation and chemical industries.  
