<HEADLINE> Hohhot Airport to Be Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Baita (White Pagoda) Airport
in this capital city of north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region is to be expanded to cope with the growing demands of both
passenger and cargo transport.
</P>
<P>
The expansion project has received approval from the Civil
Aviation Administration of China and the regional government.
</P>
<P>
The expansion, which includes the upgrading of a runway,
parking apron and the terminal building, will cost 113 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Upon its completion in June 1997, the airport will be able to
accommodate large planes such as Boeing 757s and open more
domestic routes.
</P>
<P>
The airport has been providing round-the-clock service for
medium-sized airplanes such as MP-80s and Boeing-737s since it was
chosen by the State Council as a frontier airport in 1992.
</P>
<P>
In recent years the local government has invested 200 million
yuan in upgrading airports in Hailar and Baotou as well as
Hohhot. It has replaced all the earthen runways at seven local
airports with newly-paved cement ones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
