<HEADLINE> Russian Credit Bank to Open Beijing Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Credit Bank, one of
the five leading banks in Russia, is soon to open an office in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The new office is to render credit service on the basis of
equality and mutual benefit between China and the Russian
Federation to promote bilateral trade development, said the
director of the International Development Department of the bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank, founded in 1990, is a share-holding commercial bank
with branches in all the major cities in Russia. It was the only
bank to make money payment and settlement of accounts in the 15
states of the federation in the 1995-96 period. The bank has
opened offices in Britain, Sweden, Hungary, Lebanon, Bahrain and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The world economic and financial center in the 21st Century
will move to China, which has attracted world attention with its
fast economic growth, the director said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the president of the bank expressed the wish to open
a Beijing office when Chinese Premier Li Peng visited Russia in
1995, and Li accepted the request, he said.
</P>
<P>
With enhanced co-operation among companies and enterprises
between the two countries, both sides wish to get more information
on each other's financial development, and laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
The primary task of the office is to offer information and
consultancy in these fields, the director noted.
</P>
<P>
The bank has forged close links with the Bank of China, the
Export-Import Bank of China and other leading banks, and
participated in the development of the Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
Financial circles in Russia attach great importance to the
forthcoming visit to China by Russian President Boris Yeltsin, he
said, adding the bank president and vice-president in charge of
the bank's Asian-Pacific affairs will be part of Yeltsin's
entourage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
