<HEADLINE> Macao Residents Make Four Hours of International Phone calls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Macao residents made about four
hours of international long-distance phone calls on average last
year, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
The total period of international long-distance phone calls
reached 1.70 million hours, which would translate into 70,800 days
and nights, or 191.2 years.
</P>
<P>
Most of the long-distance phone calls were made to China's
mainland and Hong Kong, both exceeding 45 million minutes. Calls to
Portugal surpassed three million minutes.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the Macao Telecommunications Company made a total
of 817.9 million Patacas (about 106.2 million US dollars) of income
last year, an increase of 14.8 percent from that of the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Macao's total telephone capacity
reached 153,300 lines, and international telephone service is
available at all telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
Macao had established international direct dialing service
(IDD) with 219 countries and regions around the world by the end
of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
