<HEADLINE> 5 Songkran Revelers Killed in Thai Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Five Thai revelers were killed
and 16 others injured on Friday, the first day of Songkran, Thai
New Year, when their pickup collided with a 10-wheel truck in
Nakhon Ratchasima province, 260 kilometers northeast of Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Police said their vehicle overtook another pickup before
crashing head-on with the ten-wheeler coming in the opposite
direction, according to a report from Nakhon Ratchsima.
</P>
<P>
Police said the pickup driver and some of the passengers were
drunk.
</P>
<P>
The revelers had been traveling around splashing people with
water to celebrate Thai New Year.
</P>
<P>
Among those killed were the pickup driver and a 10-year-old
boy.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the 10-wheeler fled the scene, police said.
