<HEADLINE> More Projects To Improve Tourism Facilities On Mount Wuyi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Four major construction projects
will be launched to improve tourism facilities in the tourism zone
around Wuyi Mountain, a famous scenic spot in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The four projects are a international conference center, a
bowling center, an entertainment complex and a water recreation
center.
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1992, the Wuyi Mountain Tourism Zone was the among
the first 11 national ones. With an area of 12 sq km, the zone is
planned to consist of six service districts and 15 subzones.
</P>
<P>
Agreements on 61 projects in the zone have been reached, with
an contractual investment of 3.6 billion yuan. Some 26 of these
projects are foreign-funded to the tune of 514 million US
dollars. A total of 28 projects have been completed.
</P>
<P>
To provide a better investment environment in the zone,
projects to improve roads, power supply and telecommunications
facilities in and around the zone have also been carried out.
</P>
</TEXT>
