<HEADLINE> Internet Brings Zhejiang Unexpected Business Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The world-wide internet has
given a Chinese hotel an amazing leap forward.
</P>
<P>
The Wanghu Hotel in Hangzhou, capital city of east China's
Zhejiang Province, has seen its business volume in the first
quarter of this year reach the equivalent of the whole of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The hotel owners say the four-fold increase is because its
information can reach more than 60 million subscribers on the
world-renowned Internet.
</P>
<P>
The hotel is one of the local companies to benefit from the
"Golden Pigeon" Project, launched by the province to publicize its
economic information on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Soon after Zhejiang Automotive Trade Corporation announced its
commercial information on the network, three foreign companies
sent representatives to the corporation to negotiate possible
cooperation in auto spares and parts.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang, one of the most affluent provinces in east China, now
regularly publicizes information on the developments of local
economic reforms and investment environment, which is accessible
to Internet subscribers in some 150 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
China has 20,000 subscribers linked to the web, which has been
a hot topic since it was first introduced into the country several
years ago.
</P>
<P>
Provincial government officials said that this project is run
by two returned overseas Chinese students, who were the first to
register a Chinese commercial information distribution center on
the network.  
</P>
</TEXT>
