<HEADLINE> Transafrica Bank Opens Branch at Entebbe Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Transafrica Bank, which started
operation here seven months ago has opened a branch at Entebbe
Airport, Uganda's sole international airport, reported the local
daily "the New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
The bank owned by the Mehta group of companies was opened by
the Permanent Secretary in Ugandan Ministry of Finance and
Economic Planning Tumusime Mutebile on Thursday.
