<HEADLINE> Chissano Favors Restoring Coop with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- President Joaquim Chissano has
expressed support for revitalizing cooperation with Russia, a
local daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
While saying good-bye to outgoing Russian Ambassador Vladimir
Korneev here on Friday, Chissano said Mozambique, being
"interdependent" with Russia in the past, should revitalize this
ties beginning in trade and the economic field.
</P>
<P>
He said his government hopes that new kind of new cooperation
should be extended to include states of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
Since independence in 1975, Mozambique had had close ties with
the ex-Soviet bloc including East European countries in
political, military, economic and cultural aspects. These links
were weakened after the collapse of the former Soviet bloc.
