<HEADLINE> Over 2,000 Students Study German in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Over 2,000 students in nine
secondary schools and over 80 students at Makerere University are
studying German in Uganda, reported the local daily "the New
Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
The language was first introduced in the university in 1965. A
degree program in German language started at the university in
1967 and it was introduced in three secondary schools, namely
Mengo, Kibuli and Aga Khan in 1979, initially taught by German
teachers sponsored by the German Academic Exchange Service
(DAAD).
</P>
<P>
Mr. H. Schott, Head of the Department of German in Makerere
University here was quoted as saying that from 1967, DAAD
continued to support the program even through difficult years
(meaning political turmoil in the 1970s and early 1980s) and the
program has gone on smoothly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
