<HEADLINE> University Co-operating With High-tech Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Nineteen young officials from
Suzhou's High-tech Industrial Development Zone in east China's
Jiangsu Province, recently completed a six-month foreign languages
training course at Nanjing University.
</P>
<P>
The prestigious university started long-term co-operation
programs with the development zone to train personnel, engage in
scientific research projects, and get involved in technology
development several years ago.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 2.5 billion US dollars, the 16-sq-km
zone was one of the earliest high-tech development zones. But,
with its rapid development, it found itself in need of more
talented and better trained personnel over recent years.
</P>
<P>
With the idea of raising the general level of education, the
development zone set up a one-million-yuan foundation for
outstanding teachers at the university, and at the same time
provided employment opportunities for graduates of Nanjing
University.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jinhua, head of the development zone, said that an
additional 100 young officials will be sent to the university for
advanced study by 1997.  
</P>
