<HEADLINE> Island Province to Promote Ten Tourism Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's sole island province of
Hainan, in south China, will promote ten tourism programs this
year featuring its tropical scenery and ethnic folk customs.
</P>
<P>
The ten programs include holidays on tropical beaches, folk
customs of ethnic minorities, leisure time spent by hot springs,
viewing tropical plants, tasting local foods, touring cultural
sights and relics, business meetings and investigation tours.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has improved both its travel facilities and services.
</P>
<P>
With eight international air routes soon to be opened by
Phoenix Airport in Sanya City, the second-biggest airport after
the Haikou Airport, all round-island tours will have Haikou and
Sanya as their starting and ending points.
</P>
<P>
The province has conducted a thorough check of its travel
services, hotels, tourist shops, and tourist spots, in accordance
with a set of tourism regulations issued last year. Those
providing poor services have been punished.
</P>
<P>
By early last March, hotels catering to overseas travelers had
accommodated over 600,000 visitors, a growth of about 40 percent
over the same period of last year, and the occupancy rate
surpassed 45 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hainan received a total of 3.26 million domestic and overseas
travelers last year, of which 287,100 were from overseas. The
province reaped 5.25 billion yuan in tourism revenues.
</P>
<P>
The three figures for this year are projected at 3.6 million,
320,000, and six billion yuan, respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
