<HEADLINE> Shougang Iron, Steel Company Earns 700 Million US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Capital Iron and Steel
Company, also known as Shougang, posted foreign exchange earnings
of nearly 700 million US dollars during the 1991-1995 period,
according to the latest official release.
</P>
<P>
The amount is equal to seven percent of the company's total
sales volume in the five years.
</P>
<P>
Last year Shougang, one of the largest iron and steel complexes
in China, earned over 230 million US dollars-worth of foreign
exchange, up from 47.7 million US dollars-worth in 1991, said the
release, according to which the company was the Chinese capital's
largest foreign exchange earner over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Between 1991 and 1995, Shougang exported 2.05 million tons of
steel rods, twisted steel, steel plates and steel billets, with
1995's exports standing at 700,000 tons of rolled steel, about 4.6
times the 1991 figure.
</P>
<P>
Shougang's exports have reached more than 40 countries and
regions in Asia, Europe, America and Africa, with top importers
including Hong Kong, Macao, the United States, Canada, the
Republic of Korea and some Southeast Asian nations in the past few
years, the release said.  
</P>
