<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 06:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Beijing Benefits from Pollution-Free Energy Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The development of pollution-free
energy resources has brought great benefits to both environmental
protection and economic growth in the suburban areas of the
Chinese capital, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Office for Rural Energy Resources said
that such programs can save more than 3 million tons of coal
annually and create 690 million yuan in profits. Moreover, these
programs also have reduced the discharge of wastes and pollutants.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that at present some 73,000 of Beijing's rural
households have set up methane-generating pits, with the annual
output of methane equalling more than 12,000 tons of standard coal.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, construction of large-scale methane-generating
projects is going on rapidly. Liuminying Village in Daxing County
built a 100-cu-m high-temperature fermenting methane-generating
project in 1993. Now the village's 240 households and local
restaurants are using piped methane for cooking.
</P>
<P>
Comprehensive utilization of methane in rural Beijing has
proved successful.
</P>
<P>
A survey among 760 rural households showed that each year they
can raise 64,000 pigs and 118,000 chickens with methane sediment,
and feed fish in 470 ha of fish ponds with liquid gas waste,
saving some 9,000 tons of fodder. The rest of the sediment can be
used in planting more than 60000 ha of vegetables and crops.
</P>
<P>
More local industrial enterprises have also devoted great
efforts to using methane-generating technology to treat industrial
waste.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the city has explored ways to make use of solar energy
in cultivating vegetables in winter. In suburban Beijing 870 ha of
greenhouses have been built, saving some 500,000 tons of coal and
saving 30 million kg of waste gas.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, rural Beijing has also set up solar energy geysers
and other facilities.
</P>
<P>
Beijing recently invested 10 million yuan in establishing a
solar energy photo-electric technology development center.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960413.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 06:32 </DATE_TIME>
