<HEADLINE> Festive Atmosphere Prevails in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Traffic in the Thai capital of
Bangkok has been flowing freely in the last two days as the
four-day Songkran (Thai New Year) holiday began Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, there has been slight congestion on main roads leading
out of Bangkok to the provinces.
</P>
<P>
Even though traffic on highways has not been as heavy as
expected, highway police, who work around the clock during the
holiday to provide assistance to motorists, have described traffic
on highways as being "slow."
</P>
<P>
No traffic disaster has been reported in the last two days.
</P>
<P>
Buses, trains and planes were booked solid weeks before the
Water Festival holiday began.
</P>
<P>
More flights have been added to Chiang Mai, Phuket and other
major resort towns to meet the demand.
</P>
<P>
Chiang Mai, known as the Rose of the North, is the best place
in the country to experience the excitement and fun of water
splashing of the Songkran Festival.
</P>
<P>
Artists from Thailand, Myanmar, Laos, Cambodia and the Dai
ethnic group in China's Yunnan province will give a cultural show
today in Chiang Mai.
</P>
<P>
In towns and other communities, there are processions of
beautiful girls, dancers, carnival floats, bands and beauty
contest. From amidst the beauty contestants, a "queen" of the
festival is chosen.
</P>
<P>
With April being one of the hottest month in Thailand, when
temperatures run as high as over 40 degrees centigrade, people,
especially youngsters, splash water on each other with whatever
utensils, including hoses connected to taps and big jars
containing water placed on pick-up trucks.
</P>
<P>
Everyone in the country is caught in a merry-making mood and
even foreign tourists get a drenching to help quench the heat.
</P>
<P>
On the morning of Songkran Day, young people gently sprinkle
scented water into the hands of the elders and parents as a mark
of respect for them.
</P>
<P>
There are also religious rites held at temples throughout the
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
