<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Trade Deficit Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's trade deficit
reached the mark of 2.69 billion US dollars during the first nine
months of the current fiscal year, an increase of 1.06 billion
dollars over the corresponding period in 1994-95.
</P>
<P>
According to the Federal Bureau of Statistics, the value of
Pakistan's exports during July 1995-March 1996 amounted to 5.901
billion dollars compared with the previous year's figure of 5.63
billion dollars, representing a total increase of 273 million
dollars and showing an increase of 4.9 percent over the
corresponding period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The imports during this period totaled 8.5 billion dollars as
against 7.3 billion dollars for the corresponding period of last
year, showing an increase of 18.3 percent. 
