<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 02:46 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Urges Equal Treatment for NATO Applicants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 12 (Xinhua) -- NATO should treat all
applicants for membership equally by allowing them to join the
alliance at the same time, Romanian President Ion Iliescu said
today.
</P>
<P>
He told visiting German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe that if
central and east European countries were not granted entry into
NATO together, relations between them would be tense and this
would not be conducive for stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
He added that Romania's membership of the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) was an aspiration shared by all political
parties in the country.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with Ruehe on Thursday, Romanian
Defense Minister Gheorghe Tinca also stressed that it would be
unacceptable if applicant countries failed to enter the alliance
together.
</P>
<P>
Romania and Hungary recently agreed to help each other to join
the alliance at the same time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
