<HEADLINE> Germany to Send 150 Police Officers to Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany will send 150 police
officers to Bosnia to serve in the United Nations international
police force patroling the fragile peace there, an Interior
Ministry spokesman confirmed here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,700 policemen from 30 countries are to be stationed in
war-ravaged Bosnia to help build up the law-enforcement system,
the Deutsche Presse Agentur reported.
</P>
<P>
The cost of dispatching the German police to Bosnia will be
shared by the Interior and Foreign Ministries. 
</P>
