<HEADLINE> Pierce Upsets Martinez at Amelia Island Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Seventh-seeded Mary Pierce of
France scored a major upset with a 5-7, 6-3, 6-2 quarter-final
victory over defending champion and top seed Conchita Martinez of
Spain at the $450,000 Bausch &AMP; Lomb Championships in Amelia
Island, Florida on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In another quarter-final pairing, second-seeded Arantxa
Sanchez Vicario of Spain defeated 13th-seeded Meredith McGrath of
the United States 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The 14th-ranked Pierce meets sixth-seeded American Mary Joe
Fernandez in one semifinal. The third-ranked Sanchez Vicario meets
eighth-seeded Irina Spirlea of Romania in Saturday's other semi.
</P>
<P>
The 13th-ranked Fernandez defeated 12th-seeded Sabine Hack of
Germany 6-4, 6-3 and the 22nd-ranked Spirlea defeated 58th-ranked
Barbara Schett of Austria 7-6 (9/7), 6-2 in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Friday marked Pierce's first quarter-final appearance in 1996
-- in all three of the other tournaments she played this year she
bowed out in the second round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
