<HEADLINE> Austrian, Polish Parliaments End Two-Day Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Austrian Parliament and a
Polish parliamentary delegation ended here today a two-day meeting
focused on European integration and security and bilateral
economic ties.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the Polish delegation stressed its
country's determination to join the EU and NATO while the
Austrians proposed the creation of a broader security system in
Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Polish delegation, led by Speaker of the House of
Representatives Jozef Zych, won broad support for Warsaw's bid for
EU and NATO membership at meetings with Austrian government
leaders.
</P>
<P>
The two parliaments planned to meet again in Warsaw next year.
</P>
