<HEADLINE> Spanish King Nominates Aznar as Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Spanish King Juan Carlos today
nominated President of the Spanish Popular Party Jose Maria Aznar
as the new prime minister after consultations with various party
leaders.
</P>
<P>
The king has informed the parliament of his nomination and
urged the legislators to vote for his nomination.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with the king today, Aznar, head of the
largest party in Spain, said he will form a new cabinet as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Aznar told the press that he will negotiate with three local
leaders of his party on the nomination in a bid to obtain their
support.
</P>
<P>
All party leaders attending the meeting expressed their support
for the nomination, saying the new government should be organized
by Aznar, whose party won the elections in March.
</P>
<P>
The outgoing Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez, also head of the
ruling Socialist Workers' Party which has been in power for 13
years, said he will adopt a "constructive" attitude toward the
government transition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
