<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 01:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng: Visit to France a Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that his visit to France has been a success both politically
and economically.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with French journalists, the visiting Chinese
premier said that he had exchanged views with French President
Jacques Chirac, Prime Minister Alain Juppe and other government
officials on a broad range of issues.
</P>
<P>
In particular, Li said, he and Chirac agreed on issues related
to the current international situation and Sino-French relations.
</P>
<P>
He said both sides shared the view that the world will be a
dangerous place if it is dominated by only one country.
</P>
<P>
The world is now becoming multipolar, he added, which will
benefit global peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Li also said that the two sides signed a number of agreements
and contracts worth a total of 2.4 billion U.S. dollars, which
have paved the way for future cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Asked about China's ties with Europe, Li said that China
attaches importance to the development of ties with Europe and is
ready to strengthen political consultations and expand trade and
economic cooperation with the continent.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is prepared to develop normal relations
with all the countries in the world, including European nations
and the United States, in line with the principles of equality,
mutual benefit and peaceful coexistence.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier, who began his five-day official visit to
France on April 9, leaves for home on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
