<HEADLINE> NATO Chief Visits Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- NATO Secretary-General Javier
Solana paid a one-day visit to Portugal today.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with Portuguese Foreign Minister Jaime Gama,
views were exchanged on NATO's eastward expansion, relations with
Russia, institutional reforms and military presence in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Solana said NATO is ready to further develop ties with Russia
while Gama reaffirmed that Portugal, as a founding member of the
alliance, will actively participate in NATO affairs and make its
own contributions.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in the Iberian nation, Solana also met with
Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio, Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres and Defense Minister Antonio Vitorino. 
