<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 01:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Expands Economic, Trade Relations with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China's northwestern Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region is expected to sponsor an export commodity
fair and hold trade talks in New Siberia in June.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jianguo, director of the Autonomous Regional Bureau of
Foreign Economic Cooperation and Trade, said that Xinjiang, which
has close economic ties with Central Asian countries, is focusing
on trade cooperation with the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the region's fifth Urumqi Economic and
Foreign Trade Talks, to be held in September, will open a special
exhibition hall for Russian products.
</P>
<P>
A survey showed that Sino-Russian business people concluded
trade volume totalling more than four million US dollars at its
fourth trade talks last September.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Xinjiang had invited officials from
the Ministry of Foreign Economic Cooperation and Trade, and
commercial counsellors from Russia and related countries, to
Xinjiang to study and explore to develop economic cooperation and
trade.
</P>
<P>
"Through the trade intercourse with Central Asian countries
over the years, we have come to see that, to further develop trade
among the Common Wealth of the Independent States, it is essential
to strengthen our cooperation with Russia," said Habay, deputy
director of the regional bureau of foreign cooperation and trade.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang concluded trade volume with Russia totalled 38.69
million US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
"Although the trade contact between Xinjiang and Russia started
later, it is promising because Xinjiang has a railway link," Wei
noted.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by the autonomous regional government, foreign trade
enterprises are positively seeking cooperation with leading
industrial enterprises and factories in Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
