<DATE_TIME> 1996-04-13 00:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Soccer Strike Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The head of Italy's soccer players'
union said on Friday that a planned serie A strike on April 20 had
been "temporarily suspended".
</P>
<P>
Sergio Campana told reporters after leaving the Italian soccer
federation's headquarters that the AIC union had decided tolift
the immediate threat of a strike because agreement had been
reached on a number of important issues.
</P>
<P>
The suspension was also agreed because the league was meeeting
government officials on April 18. Campana said the union would
meet again in the final week of April to discuss the strike which
could still be held in May.
</P>
<P>
The Italian soccer season ends on May 12.
</P>
<P>
Campana said the union had reached agreement on a key
guarantee fund to help players whose clubs folded.
</P>
<P>
Italian serie A players staged an unprecedented strike on
March 16 and 17 over a range of grievances.
</P>
<P>
They made up the lost matches last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The issues include maintaining limits on players from outside
the European Union in the wake of the European Court's recent
Bosman ruling and they are seeking the immediate abolition of
transfer fees at the end of the current season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
