<HEADLINE> Enqvist, Radulescu Reach Semifinal Indian Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Top seed and world number nine
Thomas Enqvist of Sweden and unseeded German Alex Radulescu
reached semi-finals at the 430,000 U.S. dollar Indian Open Tennis
tournament here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Enqvist downed France's Jean Phillipe Fleurian 6-3, 6-3, to
cruise into semifinals while unseeded German Alex Radulescu beat
eighth-seeded Jerome Golmard of France.
</P>
<P>
The 139th-ranked Radulescu, who upset second-seeded Wayne
Ferreira of South Africa in the second round, defeated the
96th-ranked Frenchman 4-6, 7-5, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Enqvist, who was the architect of Sweden's
thumping 5-0 win over India in the Davis Cup last week, played
excellent tennis to overcome Fleurian's challenge in just 66
minutes.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Radulescu, whose parents emigrated from Romania
to Germany when he was 15 years old, will play third-seeded Byron
Black of Zimbabwe for a place in the final of India's first ATP
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Black, ranked 32nd in the world, came back from the loss of the
first set to defeat 120th-ranked Cristiano Carritti of Italy 3-6,
6-1, 7-5 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In another quarterfinal, Jonathan Stark of the United States
defeated Australian Sandon Stolle, the son of former Australian
star Fred Stolle, 6-2, 3-6, 7-6 (7/3).
</P>
<P>
Stark, at 140 the lowest-ranked player remaining in the
tournament, will play Enqvist in the semifinal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
