<HEADLINE> World Bank To Provide $120 Million Credit for  Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of a credit equivalent to some 120 million U.S
dollars for Ethiopia's Social Rehabilitation and Development Fund
Project.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed to provide financial and technical support
to the Eastern African country's poor and mainly rural communities
and will also operate as a major component of the government's
poverty reduction program which will benefits estimated 7 million
people in Ethiopia's poorest and most isolated communities.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending arm of
the World Bank under the standard IDA terms: 40 years maturity,
10-year grace period and a 0.75 percent service charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
