<HEADLINE> US Package Bomb Kills One, Wounds Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A package bomb exploded today
in a suburban home of Plantation, Florida, killing a woman and
injuring three children, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
One of the children brought the package into the house from the
porch. When the mother opened it, the bomb exploded and killed her
immediately, a police receptionist was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Two boys, aged 7 and 15, received minor injuries and a
10-year-old girl was badly wounded in the lower part of the body.
</P>
<P>
The force of the blast blew windows and screens open on the
back side of the house.
</P>
<P>
The package had a delivery service's markings but there was no
sign any delivery company had actually put it there, the
Associated Press said, quoting police Sgt. Mike Price.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Bureau of Investigation and the U.S. Bureau of
Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms have sent an investigation team to
the scene to track down the origin and find the motive for the
explosion. 
</P>
