<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab FMs to Discuss Israeli Attack on Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the Arab
League (AL) Esmat Abdul Meguid today said that he is making
consultations with Arab foreign Ministers for holding an emergency
meeting of the AL members to deal with Israel's attack on Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
This move came on the request by Lebanon, according to the
Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Meguid condemned these attacks, describing them as
running contrary to international laws and norms.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the AL's absolute support for the Lebanese people and
their right to defend their territories.
</P>
<P>
The AL chief stressed that the bombing by Israeli warplanes of
the Lebanese capital of Beirut and its surrounding areas is a
flagrant violation of the security of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Meguid termed the Israeli aggression on Lebanon as adding
obstacles to the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
He called on the international community to condemn the brutal
Israeli aggression on Lebanon and to take all necessary measures
compelling Israel to respect the sovereignty and territorial
integrity of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Meguid also called on the international community to
exert pressure on Israel to implement U.N. Security Council
Resolution 425, which calls for an unconditional withdrawal of
Israeli troops from lebanese territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
